    "name": "Sentiment Analyzer — Master Suite",
    "description": "# Sentiment Analyzer — All Endpoints Suite\n\nA comprehensive test suite for the **Sentiment Analyzer API**, a crypto-focused platform that combines social media sentiment analysis, multi-agent reinforcement learning (MARL), evolutionary agent optimization, and real broker trading integration.\n\n## Overview\n\nThis collection covers every endpoint across the full API surface, organized into logical functional groups. Each request includes both **success** and **failure** examples to support documentation, mock server generation, and contract testing.\n\n## Base URL\n\nAll requests use the `{{base_url}}` collection variable. Set this to your environment's API root (e.g., `http://localhost:3000` or your deployed URL).\n\n## Authentication\n\nMost endpoints require an API key passed via the `X-API-Key` header or `Authorization: Bearer <token>`. Set `{{api_secret_key}}` in your environment or collection variables.\n\n## Collection Variables\n\n| Variable | Description |\n|---|---|\n| `base_url` | Root URL of the API server |\n| `api_secret_key` | API authentication key |\n| `symbol` | Crypto symbol (e.g., `BTC`, `ETH`) |\n| `competition_id` | MARL competition identifier |\n| `agent_id` | MARL agent identifier |\n| `test_id` | Backtest job identifier |\n| `tournament_id` | Evolutionary tournament identifier |\n| `credential_id` | Broker credential identifier |\n| `social_item_id` | Social media item identifier |\n\n## Folders\n\n| Folder | Description |\n|---|---|\n| **Core** | Health checks, coin data, sentiment analysis, backtesting, trending, and scraping |\n| **Social Media** | Social media item retrieval, trending topics, stats, and refresh triggers |\n| **MARL Competition** | Multi-agent competition lifecycle: start, monitor, results, and agent comparison |\n| **MARL Broker Real Trading** | Broker credential management, connection, order tracking, and emergency stop |\n| **Agent Stats & Evolutionary** | Agent performance stats, genome/genealogy, leaderboard, and evolutionary tournaments |\n| **Trading** | Live exchange integration: prices, balances, order placement, and trading stats |\n| **Admin Config** | Runtime configuration management |\n| **Paper Analytics** | Net-of-fees expectancy and paper trade reporting |\n| **Shadow Harness** | Deterministic tick-by-tick replay harness |\n| **Walk-Forward Validation** | Rolling-window strategy validation |\n| **Live Agent Orchestrator** | Live agent decision cycle and MARL policy feeding |\n| **Tournament Scheduling & Live Control** | Recurring tournament scheduling and live execution control |\n\n## Error Format\n\nAll error responses follow a consistent structure:\n```json\n{\n  \"error\": \"ERROR_CODE\",\n  \"message\": \"Human-readable description\",\n  \"details\": { ... }\n}\n```\n\n## HTTP Status Codes Used\n\n| Code | Meaning |\n|---|---|\n| 200 | OK — Request succeeded |\n| 201 | Created — Resource created |\n| 202 | Accepted — Async job queued |\n| 400 | Bad Request — Invalid parameters |\n| 401 | Unauthorized — Missing or invalid credentials |\n| 404 | Not Found — Resource does not exist |\n| 409 | Conflict — State conflict (e.g., already connected) |\n| 422 | Unprocessable Entity — Validation failed |\n| 429 | Too Many Requests — Rate limit exceeded |\n| 503 | Service Unavailable — Downstream service down |",
