      "description": "## Social Media\n\nEndpoints for retrieving, analyzing, and refreshing social media content related to crypto assets. Covers Reddit and Twitter/X data ingestion and trending topic detection.\n\n### Endpoints\n\n| Method | Path | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| GET | `/api/social-media/trending-topics` | Get trending topics across social platforms within a time window |\n| GET | `/api/social-media/items` | List social media items sorted by score or recency |\n| GET | `/api/social-media/item/:id` | Get full detail for a single social media item |\n| GET | `/api/social-media/stats` | Aggregate stats across all ingested social media content |\n| GET | `/api/trending-score/:symbol` | Get the trending score for a specific coin symbol |\n| POST | `/api/social-media/refresh` | Trigger a refresh of social media data for specified platforms and symbols |\n\n### Query Parameters\n\n- `timeWindow` — Time window in hours. Accepted values: `1`, `4`, `12`, `24`\n- `sort` — Sort order for items. Accepted values: `score`, `date`, `mentions`\n- `since_hours` — Filter items published within the last N hours\n- `limit` — Maximum number of results to return\n- `interval` — Trending score calculation interval in hours\n\n### Notes\n- Refresh requests are rate-limited. If you receive a `429`, wait for the `Retry-After` header value before retrying.\n- Social media items include engagement metrics (likes, shares, comments) and a computed sentiment score.",
