      "description": "## MARL Broker Real Trading\n\nEndpoints for managing real broker connections and live trading operations. Supports credential management, exchange connectivity, order tracking, and emergency controls.\n\n### Endpoints\n\n| Method | Path | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| GET | `/api/marl/broker/credentials` | List all saved broker credentials |\n| GET | `/api/marl/broker/credentials/picker` | Get a simplified list of credentials for UI dropdowns |\n| POST | `/api/marl/broker/connect/:id` | Connect to a broker using a saved credential |\n| GET | `/api/marl/broker/connected` | Check whether a broker is currently connected |\n| GET | `/api/marl/broker/orders/:competitionId` | List all orders placed during a competition |\n| POST | `/api/marl/broker/emergency-stop` | Immediately cancel all open orders and close all positions |\n| DELETE | `/api/marl/broker/credentials/:id` | Delete a saved broker credential |\n\n### Broker Connection Flow\n\n1. **Register credentials** — POST `/api/marl/broker/credentials`\n2. **Connect** — POST `/api/marl/broker/connect/:id`\n3. **Verify** — GET `/api/marl/broker/connected`\n4. **Trade** — Agents place orders automatically during competitions\n5. **Stop** — POST `/api/marl/broker/emergency-stop` if needed\n\n### Emergency Stop\n\nThe emergency stop endpoint is a safety mechanism that:\n- Cancels **all open orders** on the connected exchange\n- Closes **all open positions** at market price\n- Disconnects the broker session\n\nUse with caution in live trading environments.\n\n### Notes\n- Credentials are stored encrypted. API secrets are never returned in GET responses.\n- You cannot delete a credential while it is actively connected — disconnect first.\n- The `picker` endpoint returns a simplified format suitable for select/dropdown UI components.",
