      "description": "## Tournament Scheduling & Live Control\n\nEndpoints for scheduling recurring MARL tournaments and controlling live tournament execution. Supports pause, resume, stop, and real-time SSE streaming of tournament events.\n\n### Endpoints\n\n| Method | Path | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| GET | `/api/tournaments` | List all tournaments |\n| GET | `/api/tournaments/active` | List currently running tournaments |\n| GET | `/api/tournaments/:id` | Get details for a specific tournament |\n| POST | `/api/tournaments/:id/pause` | Pause a running tournament |\n| POST | `/api/tournaments/:id/resume` | Resume a paused tournament |\n| POST | `/api/tournaments/:id/stop` | Stop and finalise a tournament |\n| GET | `/api/tournaments/:id/stream` | SSE stream of live tournament events |\n| GET | `/api/tournaments/schedules` | List all tournament schedules |\n| POST | `/api/tournaments/schedules` | Create a new recurring tournament schedule |\n| GET | `/api/tournaments/schedules/:id` | Get a specific schedule |\n| PUT | `/api/tournaments/schedules/:id` | Update a schedule |\n| DELETE | `/api/tournaments/schedules/:id` | Delete a schedule |\n| POST | `/api/tournaments/schedules/:id/run-now` | Trigger an immediate run of a scheduled tournament |\n\n### Notes\n- Schedules use cron expressions for recurrence.\n- SSE stream closes when the tournament reaches a terminal state (completed, stopped).\n- A paused tournament retains all agent state and can be resumed at any time.",
      "event": [
